      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NO BAD DEED (7) stalked lead from an outside box last start before finishing second (22.86) at Geelong in a Grade 4/5 over 400m. Overdue and expected to feature again. WHIPSTICK SERENA (1) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 2 length second (23.44) over 410m at Horsham. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Can measure up. PAW INGRID (3) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at Geelong over 400m behind Paw Sherman (23.29) in a Grade 5. Shapes as one to consider.",
